OL,3,CScouts referred to police as inquest
OL,4,Cfinds boy was unlawfully killed
OL,6,FBen and two friends took a different
OL,7,Fpath from other Scouts, unsupervised
OL,8,Fby any Scout leaders, who had "lost"
OL,9,Fthe trio on the Orme.
OL,11,FBen ended up on a 50cm ledge, which
OL,12,Fwas an animal track, when he lost his
OL,13,Ffooting, slipped and fell to his death.
OL,15,FFollowing a two-month inquest at
OL,16,FManchester Civil Courts of Justice, a
OL,17,Fjury found Ben was unlawfully killed
OL,18,Fby the most senior Scout leader on the
OL,19,Ftrip, and an assistant Scout leader,
OL,20,Fand this was contributed to by neglect
OL,21,Fby The Scout Association.
