OL,3,CScouts referred to police as inquest
OL,4,Cfinds boy was unlawfully killed
OL,6,FThe inquest jury heard Ben's family
OL,7,Fwere told, "people who try and take on
OL,8,Fthe Scouts are never successful" and
OL,9,Fthat "no one can touch the Scouts"
OL,10,Fdespite it being apparent from the day
OL,11,Fof Ben's death, that things had gone
OL,12,F"horribly wrong".
OL,14,FBernard Richmond KC, told the hearing
OL,15,FBen's life could have been saved but
OL,16,Ffor the "basic failure of care" to
OL,17,Fgive simple instructions about areas
OL,18,Fto avoid and routes that were safe on
OL,19,Fthe Orme.
