OL,6,FScout leader Mr Glaister declined to
OL,7,Fanswer questions after being warned by
OL,8,Fthe coroner he did not have to answer,
OL,9,Fif the answer was to incriminate
OL,10,Fhimself.
OL,12,FThe inquest jury heard suggestions Mr
OL,13,FGlaister had believed another man,
OL,14,FBrian Garraway, group Scout leader,
OL,15,Fwas also going on the trip, only to
OL,16,Fdiscover he was not present when he
OL,17,Fgot to their campsite in Snowdonia.
