OL,6,FIt meant no suitably qualified first
OL,7,Faider was present for the trip, which
OL,8,Fbroke Scouts rules for expeditions,
OL,9,Fand the trip should not have gone
OL,10,Fahead.
OL,12,F'The family feel like they were
OL,13,Fgaslighted', says their solicitor
OL,15,FMr Glaister agreed he had not warned
OL,16,Fany of the Scouts, including Ben, not
OL,17,Fto leave the designated paths up the
OL,18,FOrme and he was not aware of the
OL,19,Fdangers of the cliff edges.
